an tell this story in terms of financial risk, but for a lot of public-comp=
any executives it probably=C2=A0<em>feels=C2=A0</em>like a story of reputat=
ional risk, less =E2=80=9Cif we own coal mines our return on equity will go=
 down=E2=80=9D and more =E2=80=9Cif we own coal mines my big shareholders w=
ill yell at me.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0If you are immune from that pressure =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0if you are a private firm whose investors are not very ESG-conscio=
us, a Middle Eastern state-owned energy company, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0then y=
ou can buy those assets cheap and make a lot of money digging up dirty coal=
. Everyone more or less understands this, but the gap is not arbitraged awa=
